{"name":"Cursebound Strike","type":"action","img":"systems/pf2e/icons/actions/TwoActions.webp","system":{"description":{"value":"<p>Your Shikigami makes a Strike at a creature within its reach. If this Strike is successful, the creature becomes Sickened 1 in addition to the normal damage of its Strike. If the Strike was a critical hit, the creature becomes Sickened 2 instead. Cursebound Strike can&rsquo;t be used again for 1d4 rounds.</p>"},"source":{"value":""},"traits":{"value":[],"rarity":"common","custom":""},"rules":[],"slug":null,"schema":{"version":0.794,"lastMigration":{"datetime":"2022-10-16T02:50:21.266-04:00","version":{"schema":null,"foundry":"10.287","system":"4.2.6"}}},"actionType":{"value":"action"},"actionCategory":{"value":"offensive"},"actions":{"value":2},"requirements":{"value":""},"trigger":{"value":""},"deathNote":false},"effects":[],"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.6zrh4qzQaGqZPKnc"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"pf2e","systemVersion":"4.2.6","coreVersion":"10.287","createdTime":1665903021270,"modifiedTime":1673134186496,"lastModifiedBy":"ChAfHXWjGQIj5GUP"},"ownership":{"default":0,"ChAfHXWjGQIj5GUP":3},"folder":null,"sort":0,"_id":"6jlM5OCxC8rYDjLP"}
{"name":"Fascinating Kagura","type":"action","img":"systems/pf2e/icons/actions/TwoActions.webp","system":{"description":{"value":"<p>You show the steps to a quick and frantic dance, your own divine energies causing a burst of color and shapes to augment your steps. Make a Religion check against the Will DC of one creature that is within 30 feet and observing you, with the following results. If the situation demands the immediate attention of the creature, such as in combat, then this activity also gains the Incapacitation trait.</p>\n<p><strong>Critical Success</strong> The creature is unaffected.<br><strong>Success</strong> The creature is fascinated by you until the start of your next turn.<br><strong>Failure</strong> The creature is dazzled and fascinated by you until the start of your next turn.<br><strong>Critical Failure</strong> The creature is swept up in the visions and sounds of the deities&rsquo; revelry portrayed in your dance, becoming confused and dazzled until the end of your next turn.</p>\n<p>Regardless of the results, the creature is then immune to your Fascinating Kagura activity for one hour. If you are an expert in Religion, you can target up to two creatures; if you&rsquo;re a master you can target up to four; and if you&rsquo;re legendary, you can target up to 6 creatures.</p>"},"source":{"value":""},"traits":{"value":["divine","enchantment","hb_kannagi","visual"],"rarity":"common","custom":""},"rules":[],"slug":null,"schema":{"version":0.794,"lastMigration":{"datetime":"2023-01-11T02:59:09.992-05:00","version":{"schema":null,"foundry":"10.287","system":"4.2.6"}}},"actionType":{"value":"action"},"actionCategory":{"value":"offensive"},"actions":{"value":2},"requirements":{"value":""},"trigger":{"value":""},"deathNote":false},"effects":[],"ownership":{"default":0,"ChAfHXWjGQIj5GUP":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.ncxbWqjRLOYYPeH1"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"pf2e","systemVersion":"4.2.6","coreVersion":"10.287","createdTime":1673423950000,"modifiedTime":1673426143685,"lastModifiedBy":"ChAfHXWjGQIj5GUP"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"_id":"KojFNygLe7KCPfCY"}
{"name":"Purification Circle","type":"action","img":"systems/pf2e/icons/actions/ThreeActions.webp","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.DeRzkJyzkpr94zue"}},"system":{"description":{"value":"<p>Divine magic flows through your gohei, purifying your allies of their conditions. All allies within the emanation reduce their frightened, clumsy, enfeebled, sickened, and confused values by 1. Additionally your allies gain the benefit of your Gohei&rsquo;s minor manifestation against poison, disease, and necromancy effects until the end of your next turn.</p>"},"source":{"value":""},"traits":{"value":["abjuration","divine","hb_kannagi"],"rarity":"common","custom":"Kannagi"},"rules":[],"slug":null,"schema":{"version":0.794,"lastMigration":{"datetime":"2023-01-07T18:30:14.716-05:00","version":{"schema":0.769,"foundry":"10.287","system":"4.2.6"}}},"actionType":{"value":"action"},"actionCategory":{"value":""},"actions":{"value":3},"requirements":{"value":""},"trigger":{"value":""},"deathNote":false,"frequency":{"max":1,"per":"day"}},"ownership":{"default":0,"ChAfHXWjGQIj5GUP":3},"_stats":{"systemId":"pf2e","systemVersion":"4.2.6","coreVersion":"10.287","createdTime":1673134214722,"modifiedTime":1673423419271,"lastModifiedBy":"ChAfHXWjGQIj5GUP"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"_id":"R6em5c4AQGbX9LLO"}
{"name":"Personal Spy","type":"action","img":"systems/pf2e/icons/actions/OneAction.webp","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.tWdQRYTzeUjOxafP"}},"system":{"description":{"value":"<p>You can use your shikigami as an espionage tool. As long as you are within 100 feet of your familiar, you can hear as though you were standing next to it. This effect lasts until the start of your next turn, and can be sustained for up to 10 minutes.</p>"},"source":{"value":""},"traits":{"value":[],"rarity":"common","custom":"Kannagi"},"rules":[],"slug":null,"schema":{"version":0.794,"lastMigration":{"datetime":"2023-01-07T18:30:13.174-05:00","version":{"schema":0.769,"foundry":"10.287","system":"4.2.6"}}},"actionType":{"value":"action"},"actionCategory":{"value":""},"actions":{"value":1},"requirements":{"value":""},"trigger":{"value":""},"deathNote":false,"frequency":{"max":1,"per":"PT1H"}},"ownership":{"default":0,"ChAfHXWjGQIj5GUP":3},"_stats":{"systemId":"pf2e","systemVersion":"4.2.6","coreVersion":"10.287","createdTime":1673134213179,"modifiedTime":1673134213179,"lastModifiedBy":"ChAfHXWjGQIj5GUP"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"_id":"Tf7cnvTY7Y0Vkwpe"}
{"name":"Bolts From On High","type":"action","img":"systems/pf2e/icons/actions/TwoActions.webp","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.DDN5VcF3lj353y4h"}},"system":{"description":{"value":"<p><strong>Requirement</strong> You have at least 1 unspent spell slot.</p>\n<p>You charge a single arrow with divine magic, consuming one of your spell slots, before firing it into the sky. A moment later, a hail of golden bolts sail back down in reply. These arrows crash down in a straight line that stretches 60 feet from you. All enemies within the area take 2d6 damage per level of the spellslot you consumed to use Bolts from on High, with a basic Reflex save against your spell DC. The damage is the same type as your Minor Manifestation.</p>"},"source":{"value":""},"traits":{"value":["hb_kannagi"],"rarity":"common","custom":""},"rules":[],"slug":null,"schema":{"version":0.794,"lastMigration":{"datetime":"2023-01-07T18:29:37.596-05:00","version":{"schema":0.769,"foundry":"10.287","system":"4.2.6"}}},"actionType":{"value":"action"},"actionCategory":{"value":"offensive"},"actions":{"value":2},"requirements":{"value":""},"trigger":{"value":""},"deathNote":false},"ownership":{"default":0,"ChAfHXWjGQIj5GUP":3},"_stats":{"systemId":"pf2e","systemVersion":"4.2.6","coreVersion":"10.287","createdTime":1673134177603,"modifiedTime":1673423413655,"lastModifiedBy":"ChAfHXWjGQIj5GUP"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"_id":"WkAQPtkmMW9NA0KT"}
{"name":"Cleansing Kagura","type":"action","img":"systems/pf2e/icons/actions/TwoActions.webp","system":{"description":{"value":"<p>You begin to preform a dance of slow and precise movements, meant to calm the divine and lift their spirits. Make a Religion counteract check against the frightened, fleeing, or fascinated condition on one ally. If you are an expert in Religion, you can target two allies; if you&rsquo;re a master you can target four; and if you&rsquo;re legendary you can target any number of allies. Afterwards, the target is then immune to your Kagura: Preface activity for one hour.</p>"},"source":{"value":""},"traits":{"value":["divine","enchantment","hb_kannagi","visual"],"rarity":"common","custom":""},"rules":[],"slug":null,"schema":{"version":0.794,"lastMigration":{"datetime":"2023-01-11T02:49:40.584-05:00","version":{"schema":null,"foundry":"10.287","system":"4.2.6"}}},"actionType":{"value":"action"},"actionCategory":{"value":"interaction"},"actions":{"value":2},"requirements":{"value":""},"trigger":{"value":""},"deathNote":false},"effects":[],"ownership":{"default":0,"ChAfHXWjGQIj5GUP":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.ioCS5ht417MNkRnM"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"pf2e","systemVersion":"4.2.6","coreVersion":"10.287","createdTime":1673423380589,"modifiedTime":1673424776161,"lastModifiedBy":"ChAfHXWjGQIj5GUP"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"_id":"eLLyTUGAIDGQeMfn"}
{"name":"Divine Shot","type":"action","img":"systems/pf2e/icons/actions/ThreeActions.webp","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.9gs0xEHsNSluZvYx"}},"system":{"description":{"value":"<p><strong>Requirement</strong> You are weilding a bow.</p>\n<p>You Cast a Spell that requires 1 or 2 actions and requires a spell attack roll. The effects of the spell do not take place immediately, but are imbued in an arrow you are holding. Make a Strike with the required weapon. Your spell flies with the ammunition, using your Strike to determine the results of both the Strike and the spell. This counts as two attacks for your multiple attack penalty, but you don&rsquo;t increase your penalty until after you&rsquo;ve completed both attacks.</p>"},"source":{"value":""},"traits":{"value":["attack","divine","evocation","hb_kannagi"],"rarity":"common","custom":"Kannagi"},"rules":[],"slug":null,"schema":{"version":0.794,"lastMigration":{"datetime":"2023-01-07T18:29:55.835-05:00","version":{"schema":0.769,"foundry":"10.287","system":"4.2.6"}}},"actionType":{"value":"action"},"actionCategory":{"value":"offensive"},"actions":{"value":3},"requirements":{"value":""},"trigger":{"value":""},"deathNote":false},"ownership":{"default":0,"ChAfHXWjGQIj5GUP":3},"_stats":{"systemId":"pf2e","systemVersion":"4.2.6","coreVersion":"10.287","createdTime":1673134195839,"modifiedTime":1673423436810,"lastModifiedBy":"ChAfHXWjGQIj5GUP"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"_id":"nM3uKyr3k5ctImLo"}
{"name":"Combat Form","type":"action","img":"systems/pf2e/icons/actions/ThreeActions.webp","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.vTIi3vVz5nQOQaVV"}},"system":{"description":{"value":"<p>With a flurry of enchanted paper, your shikigami takes on a bestial form. Your shikigami becomes a young animal companion of your choice. If your deity has an animal strongly associated with it, such as crows and Hei Feng, then your shikigami&rsquo;s combat form must match your deity&rsquo;s aspect. Your shikigami&rsquo;s combat form is also trained in Athletics, Acrobatics, Stealth, and Thievery, and it cannot benefit from your Hidden Nature Miracle.</p>\n<p>At level 9, your shikigami becomes a mature animal companion while in its combat form, and at level 11 it becomes your choice of a nimble or savage mature animal.</p>\n<p>This effect lasts for up to 1 minute. You can Command an Animal to give your shikigami 2 actions as part of the Combat Form activity. If your shikigami is reduced to 0 hit points while in its combat form, its body disperses in a flurry of scattering papers and leaves your familiar behind in its place, unconscious.</p>"},"source":{"value":""},"traits":{"value":[],"rarity":"common","custom":"Kannagi"},"rules":[],"slug":null,"schema":{"version":0.794,"lastMigration":{"datetime":"2023-01-07T18:29:39.821-05:00","version":{"schema":0.769,"foundry":"10.287","system":"4.2.6"}}},"actionType":{"value":"action"},"actionCategory":{"value":"interaction"},"actions":{"value":3},"requirements":{"value":""},"trigger":{"value":""},"deathNote":false,"frequency":{"max":1,"per":"PT1H"}},"ownership":{"default":0,"ChAfHXWjGQIj5GUP":3},"_stats":{"systemId":"pf2e","systemVersion":"4.2.6","coreVersion":"10.287","createdTime":1673134179826,"modifiedTime":1673134179826,"lastModifiedBy":"ChAfHXWjGQIj5GUP"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"_id":"pIbFdzHknR2wLXL7"}
{"name":"O-Mikuji","type":"action","img":"systems/pf2e/icons/actions/FreeAction.webp","system":{"description":{"value":"<p>You&rsquo;ve learned how to perform a divination ritual using a technique from Minkai where your fortune will appear inscribed on a piece of paper. A petitioner must ask for a divination regarding a particular encounter, such as a diplomatic meeting with the town chief or the first strike against a particular enemy. After performing a 10 minute ritual, you roll a d20 with the following results. This effect counts as either a Fortune or Misfortune effect, depending on the result. The result is automatically applied the first time the petitioner triggers a skill check related to their divination.</p>\n<p><strong>O-Mijuki Fortune Table</strong></p>\n<table style=\"width: 100%; height: 102px;\" border=\"1\"><colgroup><col style=\"width: 8.61921%;\"><col style=\"width: 91.3808%;\"></colgroup>\n<tbody>\n<tr style=\"height: 17px;\">\n<td style=\"height: 17px;\">1</td>\n<td style=\"height: 17px;\">&nbsp;Great Misfotune - Roll twice for your skill check, taking the worse result</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 17px;\">\n<td style=\"height: 17px;\">2-4</td>\n<td style=\"height: 17px;\">&nbsp;Moderate Misfortune - You gain a -2 circumstance penalty to the triggering skill check</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 17px;\">\n<td style=\"height: 17px;\">5-10</td>\n<td style=\"height: 17px;\">&nbsp;Minor Misfortune - You gain a -1 circumstance penalty to the triggering skill check</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 17px;\">\n<td style=\"height: 17px;\">11-16</td>\n<td style=\"height: 17px;\">Minor Luck - You gain a +1 circumstance bonus to the triggering skill check</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 17px;\">\n<td style=\"height: 17px;\">17-19</td>\n<td style=\"height: 17px;\">&nbsp;Moderate Luck - You gain a +2 circumstance bonus to the triggering skill check</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 17px;\">\n<td style=\"height: 17px;\">20</td>\n<td style=\"height: 17px;\">&nbsp;Great Luck - Roll twice for your skill check, taking the better result</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>Each petitioner can only receive a divination result once per day. You can dispel a fortune of Minor Misfortune or Minor Luck by having the petitioner entrust their result to you, before tying the slip of paper their fortune appeared on to a tree.</p>"},"source":{"value":""},"traits":{"value":["divination","divine","downtime","hb_kannagi","manipulate"],"rarity":"common","custom":""},"rules":[],"slug":null,"schema":{"version":0.794,"lastMigration":{"datetime":"2022-10-16T03:05:58.742-04:00","version":{"schema":null,"foundry":"10.287","system":"4.2.6"}}},"actionType":{"value":"free"},"actionCategory":{"value":"interaction"},"actions":{"value":null},"requirements":{"value":""},"trigger":{"value":""},"deathNote":false},"effects":[],"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.eGtG9cfFGJxBG3cx"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"pf2e","systemVersion":"4.2.6","coreVersion":"10.287","createdTime":1665903958746,"modifiedTime":1673423433118,"lastModifiedBy":"ChAfHXWjGQIj5GUP"},"ownership":{"default":0,"ChAfHXWjGQIj5GUP":3},"folder":null,"sort":0,"_id":"pWQhO57yBNj5Jfxt"}
{"name":"Protective Screen","type":"action","img":"systems/pf2e/icons/actions/TwoActions.webp","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.GImquAEgJeRqMhid"}},"system":{"description":{"value":"<p><strong>Cost</strong> 1 empowered ofuda</p>\n<hr>\n<p>You launch your ofuda into the air, causing it to hover and conjure a 10-foot wide wall of thin translucent light. Enemy ranged attacks that pass through the wall suffer a -2 circumstance penalty to their attack rolls. Any enemy that attempts to pass through the screen takes a -5 foot circumstance penalty to their Speed for that movement. The screen lasts for 1 minute and can be moved up to 10 feet once per turn by spending an action that has the Concentrate trait.</p>"},"source":{"value":""},"traits":{"value":["abjuration","divine","hb_kannagi"],"rarity":"common","custom":"Kannagi"},"rules":[],"slug":null,"schema":{"version":0.794,"lastMigration":{"datetime":"2023-01-07T18:29:54.480-05:00","version":{"schema":0.769,"foundry":"10.287","system":"4.2.6"}}},"actionType":{"value":"action"},"actionCategory":{"value":""},"actions":{"value":2},"requirements":{"value":""},"trigger":{"value":""},"deathNote":false},"ownership":{"default":0,"ChAfHXWjGQIj5GUP":3},"_stats":{"systemId":"pf2e","systemVersion":"4.2.6","coreVersion":"10.287","createdTime":1673134194486,"modifiedTime":1673423425035,"lastModifiedBy":"ChAfHXWjGQIj5GUP"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"_id":"sW8dH0keaD49mbLk"}
{"name":"Divine Barrier","type":"action","img":"systems/pf2e/icons/actions/Reaction.webp","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.xUJ7ME4b0HGN7qZh"}},"system":{"description":{"value":"<p><strong>Cost</strong> 1 empowered ofuda</p>\n<p><strong>Trigger</strong> You or an ally within 30 feet would take damage from a Strike or Spell</p>\n<hr>\n<p>Your ofuda fly out to encircle the target before they can come to harm, erecting a magical barrier of protection. The target gains temporary hit points equal to your level. These temporary Hit Points are applied before the target takes damage from the triggering effect and last until the start of your next turn.</p>"},"source":{"value":""},"traits":{"value":["abjuration","divine","hb_kannagi"],"rarity":"common","custom":"Kannagi"},"rules":[],"slug":null,"schema":{"version":0.794,"lastMigration":{"datetime":"2023-01-07T18:29:51.868-05:00","version":{"schema":0.769,"foundry":"10.287","system":"4.2.6"}}},"actionType":{"value":"reaction"},"actionCategory":{"value":"defensive"},"actions":{"value":null},"requirements":{"value":""},"trigger":{"value":""},"deathNote":false,"frequency":{"max":1,"per":"PT1M"}},"ownership":{"default":0,"ChAfHXWjGQIj5GUP":3},"_stats":{"systemId":"pf2e","systemVersion":"4.2.6","coreVersion":"10.287","createdTime":1673134191873,"modifiedTime":1673423442116,"lastModifiedBy":"ChAfHXWjGQIj5GUP"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"_id":"tqIH7mtT9gIMfhp3"}
